A common insect on the centra] plateau of Guatemala and Mexico; it ranges from Northern Mexico right down to the State of Panama, but becomes rarer southwards. The narrow annulus is usually sanguineous or dilute castaneous; but in some specimens it is bordered externally with black and in others it is partly obliterated. In this and the following three species the elytra are deeply foveate on the disc before the middle, and the third joint of the antennae is much longer than the second. We figure a
